AddressInfo.Title: Värmskog Café
AddressInfo.AccessComments: This charger is a small power contact on the first parking space on Värmskog's café's parking lot, across from the school. You will find several motor warming power contacts. The leftmost of these has a red Mennekes-Type2-contact hanging out of the box.  Inside the box you will find 2 regular 10A/220v power plugs. There are two fuses and two clock timer switches. Rotate the clock timer switches to turn the power on for the respective contact. There is a sign saying that charging costs 50 SEK, payable to the local social society that runs the café. Pay to Swedish account nr. 250-9065 including the car licence plate in the transaction field. Receiver: Värmskog bygdegårdsförening.

GeneralComments: 2 x 220v/10 A Euro plugs, 1 x Mennekes
